  "text": "The ext_authz filter in Envoy (v1.31.2) implements external authorization with bypass and passthrough logic across HTTP and network protocols. The implementation is split into HTTP-specific and shared common components.\n\n**Per-Route Bypass Configuration:**\nThe FilterConfigPerRoute class (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h) implements per-route configuration that includes a `disabled` field. This allows routes to bypass ext_authz checks via the ExtAuthzPerRoute protobuf message. The disabled flag is accessed through FilterConfigPerRoute::disabled().\n\n**Authorization Decision Caching and Route Cache Clearing:**\nThe FilterConfig class (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h) maintains a clear_route_cache_ field that controls whether route cache is cleared based on authorization responses. When auth returns OK status with header modifications, the filter calls decoder_callbacks_->downstreamCallbacks()->clearRouteCache() (ext_authz.cc:441) to allow the external authorization service to affect routing decisions.\n\n**Immediate Response Path:**\nThe Filter class implements the core request/response flow:\n- decodeHeaders() (ext_authz.cc:226-277): Entry point that checks skip_check_ flag from getPerRouteFlags() to determine bypass. If disabled, returns Continue without calling the authorization service.\n- getPerRouteFlags() (ext_authz.cc:810-827): Resolves the most specific per-filter configuration from the route to determine if the filter should be skipped.\n- initiateCall() (ext_authz.cc:171-224): Initiates the authorization call by creating a CheckRequest and invoking client_->check().\n- onComplete() (ext_authz.cc:403-769): Handles the authorization response based on CheckStatus (OK, Denied, or Error). On OK status, applies header mutations, query parameter modifications, and calls continueDecoding().\n- continueDecoding() (ext_authz.cc:800-808): Sets filter_return_ to ContinueDecoding and continues the filter chain.\n\n**Authorization Service Clients:**\nTwo client implementations support different authorization service protocols:\n- GrpcClientImpl (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_grpc_impl.h/cc): Communicates with gRPC authorization services.\n- RawHttpClientImpl (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_http_impl.h/cc): Communicates with HTTP authorization services.\n\nBoth implement the Client interface (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz.h) which defines the check() method that asynchronously calls the authorization service and invokes RequestCallbacks::onComplete() with the Response.\n\n**Request Construction:**\nCheckRequestUtils (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/check_request_utils.h/cc) constructs CheckRequest protobuf messages by extracting HTTP headers, metadata, and request attributes, supporting both request body buffering and header filtering.\n\n**Network Filter:**\nA parallel network-layer implementation (source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/) provides TCP-level authorization with similar bypass and error handling mechanisms.\n\nThe complete authorization flow: (1) filter receives request, (2) checks if disabled via per-route config (bypass), (3) initiates authorization call if not bypassed, (4) receives authorization decision via onComplete callback, (5) either continues decoding on OK or sends immediate response on Denied/Error, (6) optionally clears route cache on OK with header modifications for immediate passthrough."
}

